<exercise checkit-seed="0002" checkit-slug="E3" checkit-title="Solving linear systems">
  <statement>
    <p>
Consider the following 
vector equation. <me>x_{1} \left[\begin{array}{c}
-5 \\
-3 \\
-1 \\
0
\end{array}\right] + x_{2} \left[\begin{array}{c}
-3 \\
-2 \\
3 \\
-1
\end{array}\right] + x_{3} \left[\begin{array}{c}
18 \\
11 \\
0 \\
1
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{c}
-14 \\
-9 \\
8 \\
-3
\end{array}\right]</me>
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
Explain how to find a simpler
          
          vector equation
that has the same solution set.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
Explain how to find the solution set of this simpler
          
          vector equation.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </statement>

  <answer>
      <me>\mathrm{RREF}\left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
-5 &amp; -3 &amp; 18 &amp; -14 \\
-3 &amp; -2 &amp; 11 &amp; -9 \\
-1 &amp; 3 &amp; 0 &amp; 8 \\
0 &amp; -1 &amp; 1 &amp; -3
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; -3 &amp; 1 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; -1 &amp; 3 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right]</me>
      <p>The solution set is <m> \left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
3 \, a + 1 \\
a + 3 \\
a
\end{array}\right] \,\middle|\, a \in\mathbb R \right\} </m>.</p>
  </answer>
</exercise>
